I came out and I couldn't believe the damage. and they were leading people to the light. People were shouting, 'Can I help. A checkout lady was hit with a cash register. Part of the roof was coming off, he said. Rick Snider was in the bakery aisle of a supermarket. In the jewelry business, the vault is the safest place, he said. The next thing I knew, glass was breaking and I was rolling on the ground, he recalled. Employees at a jewelry store huddled in the vault while the shop came down around them. 